ttps://isrc.iscas.ac.cn/gitlab/mirrors/git.yoctoproject.org/linux-yocto/-/commit/d0736af81151cb6213825034da0e09a7e4ad20ea\">kbuild: generate Module.symvers only when vmlinux exists</a><br>\nsay: \"A problem is that 'make modules' creates Module.symvers even without<br>\nvmlinux. In this case, that warning is suppressed since Module.symvers<br>\nalready exists in spite of its incomplete content.</p>\n<p>The incomplete (i.e. invalid) Module.symvers should not be created.</p>\n<p>This commit changes the second pass of modpost to dump symbols into<br>\nmodules-only.symvers. The final Module.symvers is created by<br>\nconcatenating vmlinux.symvers and modules-only.symvers if both exist.\"</p>\n<p>Mine issue: why ERROR: modpost: missing MODULE_LICENSE() in /root/bento/hello_ll/rust/kernel/hello_ll.o? how fix?</p>",
